title: fanoutqa: Who were the directors of movies that grossed over $700 million in 2023, and when did they direct their first movie? (Sort the directors from the one who directed their first movie earliest to the most recent.) (870881b3ef7e2866)

chat_history.content: Who were the directors of movies that grossed over $700 million in 2023, and when did they direct their first movie? (Sort the directors from the one who directed their first movie earliest to the most recent.)

I do not have access to the current year yet, so here is the list sorted from the earliest directorial debut to the latest for the year 2022:

- James Cameron, *Avatar: The Way of Water* (2022) and *Piranha II: The Spawning* (1981)
- Baz Luhrmann, *Elvis* (2022) and *Strictly Ballroom* (1992)
- James Wan, *Aquaman and the Last Reef* (2022) and *Stygian* (2000)
- David Yates, *Fantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore* (2022) and *The Tailor of Panama* (2001)
- Patrick Read Johnson, *Super Pets* (2022) and *Spaced Invaders* (1990)
- Colin Trevorrow, *Jurassic World: Dominion* (2022) and *Safety Not Guaranteed* (2012)
- Tom Harper, *The Aeronauts* (2019) and *The Scouting Book for Boys* (2009)
- Dan Trachtenberg, *Prey* (2022) and *10 Cloverfield Lane* (2016)
- Dome Karukoski, *The Berlin Patient* (2022) and *The Home of Dark Butterflies* (2008)
- Taika Waititi, *Thor: Love and Thunder* (2022) and *Eagle vs. Shark* (2007)
- Jeff Fowler, *Sonic the Hedgehog 2* (2022) and *Gopher Broke* (2004)
- Jon Watts, *The Marvels* (2022) and *Clown* (2014)
- Patrick Wilson, *Insidious: The Red Door* (2023) and *Insidious: Chapter 3* (2015)
